The paper proposes a new auction mechanism that accommodates non-additive trader preferences, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational aspects of the auction mechanism, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed mechanism in terms of economic efficiency, which is a topic in economics and computer science (cs.EC).
